Method      What the Method Returns
hour        A number representing the hour in 24-hour (e,g., 21 for 9 p.m.)
min         The number of minutes past the hour
sec         The number of seconds pat the minute
usec        The number o microseconds pat the seconds (there are 1,000,000) microseconds per second
day         The number of the day in the month
mday        Synonym ofr the day method, considered to be "month" day
wday        The day of the day in terms of the week (Sunday is o, Saturday is 6)
yday        The number of the day in terms of the year
month       The number of the month of the date (e.g., 11 for November)
zone        Returns the name of the time zone associated with the time
utc?        Returns true of false depending on if the time/date is in the UTC/GMT time zone or not
gmt?        Synonym of the utc? method for those who prefer to use the term GMT
